Paper: hep-th/0106153

Date: 2001-06-18

Title: N=8 matter coupled AdS_3 supergravities

Authors: H. Nicolai, H. Samtleben

Comments: 11 pages, LaTeX2e

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B514 (2001) 165-172

Following the recent construction of maximal (N=16) gauged supergravity inthree dimensions, we derive gauged D=3, N=8 supergravities in three dimensionsas deformations of the corresponding ungauged theories with scalar manifoldsSO(8,n)/(SO(8)x SO(n)). As a special case, we recover the N=(4,4) theories withlocal SO(4) = SO(3)_L x SO(3)_R, which reproduce the symmetries and masslessspectrum of D=6, N=(2,0) supergravity compactified on AdS_3 x S^3.